what is css?
css is cascading style sheet.

html provides structure,skeleton,description,semantics.
style sheet is a sheet in which add the value to the properties,like bg-color = red
color = pink
border = 1 px

what do u mean by cascading?
cascading means which property have to pick, means in <p> u tell the bg-color = yellow
then bg-color = purple
bg-color = brown
so, which property have to pick .

now the 4 factors on which we can decide which property have to pick or not.
==>Browser Support: Works across target browsers.
==>Flexibility: Adapts to responsive layouts.
==>Performance: Renders fast without lag.
==>Maintenance: Keeps code clean and scalable.

