the flex-wrap: wrap; means when u "inspect" u squeeze teh webpage, boxes the width size will be decrease, but if u apply flex-wrap: wrap;this will maintain the width until the space is avalibale.
flex-wrap has different values, called wrap,nowrap,warp-reverse, the boxes color will be in reverse oder color, when u squeeze it.
now, what is flex-flow --> 
<!-- Summary
- **`flex-flow`** is a shorthand property in CSS.  
- It combines **`flex-direction`** (row, column, etc.) and **`flex-wrap`** (wrap, nowrap, wrap-reverse).  
- Saves you from writing both separately.  

###  Syntax
```css
flex-flow: <flex-direction> <flex-wrap>;
```

###  Examples
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-flow: row wrap;       /* Horizontal + wrapping */
}

.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-flow: column nowrap;  /* Vertical + no wrapping */
}

