**
### 📌 Summary
- **`align-content`** controls how **multiple flex lines** are spaced along the **cross axis**.  
- It only works when items **wrap** (`flex-wrap: wrap` or `wrap-reverse`) and there is **extra space** in the container.  
- If you have just one line of items, it has **no effect**.  
### ⚙️ Syntax
```css
align-content: flex-start | flex-end | center | space-between | space-around | space-evenly | stretch;
### 🧩 Values
- `flex-start` → lines packed at the start  
- `flex-end` → lines packed at the end  
- `center` → lines packed in the middle  
- `space-between` → equal space between lines, none at edges  
- `space-around` → equal space around each line  
- `space-evenly` → equal space between and around lines  
- `stretch` → lines stretch to fill the container  
👉 Difference from `align-items`:  
- `align-items` = aligns **items within a single line**.  
- `align-content` = aligns **the lines themselves** when wrapping occurs.  

so,far studied in flex-box, which has flex-container and flex-items==
in flex-container==                      in flex-items==
display                                  order
flex-direction                           flex-grow
flex-wrap                                flex-shrink
flex-flow                                flex-basis
justify-content                          flex
align-items                              align-self
align-content

NOW,MEDIA QUERY-
what is a responsive design- it is a design when u see websites like code help, on pc, it will look like good, when the isze decreases when u see in phone it also looks good, this good actually means the etxt, video,image,is not missing when u see in different devices, but it shifted , still looks good, this is called responsive design.
now, media query is to  apply css on different devices with different display is u can do with help of media query.
syntax-
<style>
        .box{
            background-color: hotpink;
            border: dotted 5px purple;
            height: 500px;
            width: 500px;
        }
            @media  (max-width:400px){
                .box{
                    background-color: brown;
                    
                }
                
            }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="box">
        This is Muskan.
    </div>
, write this, and see, 0-500 is brown color, and after 500, it is pink color, in inspect.
also,@media (min-width:200px) and (max-width:400px){
                .box{
                    background-color: darkslategray;
                }
            }
now, if all the <div> elements share the same class name, then the CSS you define for that class will apply to all of them.
next,if u see any website in laptop, the video atright side(row), if u see the same website in phone, the video will at bottom(column),this is a good concept, and how can we achieve it , by doing flex-direction: columnn if the width (min and max) to a specific range, it will show the text, box, etc, in column the syntax -
    <style>
        .container{
            height: 400px;
            width: 400px;
            border: 5px solid deeppink;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: row;
            
        }
        .box{
            height: 200px;
            width: 100px;
            border: 3px solid black;
            margin: 4px;
            padding: 4px;
            background-color: aqua;
        }
        @media (min-width:200px) and (max-width:500px){
            .container{
                flex-direction: column;
            }
        }

    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="box">box1</div>
        <div class="box">box2</div>
        <div class="box">box3</div>
        <div class="box">box4</div>
    </div>
    
now, ,min-width: 200px means (0-199) and max-width: 500px means (200-500)


NOW,SHADOWS IN CSS, -
can render shadow on web page , like in a box, u can render shadow, and in a text u can also render it. 
There are 2 types of shadows - Box and Text shadows.
** if there are 2 container-parent(container) and child(box), so, u have to bring the child box to center, so, do changes in container that's parent one, like 
 .container{
            width: 100%;
            height: 1000px;
            border: 5px solid black;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
},
donot add justify-content to box , add it to container.
and even, u should know that container is flex container and the items in it, is flex-items, so,the properties it is like that,
in flex-container==                      in flex-items==
display                                  order
flex-direction                           flex-grow
flex-wrap                                flex-shrink
flex-flow                                flex-basis
justify-content                          flex
align-items                              align-self
align-content

, when add the shadows there are offsets, like x-offset and y-offset, syntax-
 /*box-shadow: 35px 70px black; */
            /*box-shadow: -70px 20px black;*/
            box-shadow: 20px -45px black;
, - means the opposite side,the more the pixel , more width of shadow, first x-offset y-offset color
'-' means the opposite direction , it has no role in increasing/decreasing the pixel-size.
,  box-shadow: 20px 15px 10px brown ; now, it means x-offset y-offset blur-radius color
if , box-shadow: 20px 15px -10px brown ;
        }
means in o/p- there will not be any box-shadow, as blur radius donot exist.
now,box-shadow: 10px 15px 20px 65px brown;
the fourth-65px is spread radius, upto which extent the shadow will spread.
**the term pixel values in CSS (like 100px, 1000px) can technically be any large number.
now, by default the shadow is outside, but if u want the shadow inside, so, the syntax-
 box-shadow: inset 10px 15px blue;
by adding a keyword inset.
now, if u want to add the multiple shadows, the syntax is like-
box-shadow: 5px 8px red,14px 18px lightskyblue;
o/p, firstly the first shadow applied and the  second shadow.
**now, important thing, if u are making a web page, and later u realise it that the color is not suitable and u want to change so, so, use variable , it is like an empty box,
syntax-
.box{
            --primary-color: beige;
            --custom-width: 570px;
        
            width: var(--custom-width);
            height: 700px;
            margin: 3px;
            padding: 3px;
            border: 3px solid black;
            background-color: var(--primary-color);
}
now, this primary- color and custom-width is only utilised in specific barces only in box, not the container, or other braces, is there any other way to utilise it on the whole web page,yes
syntax-
:root{
            --primary-color: beige;
            --custom-width: 570px

        }

